    public interface TreeCellContribution<T>
extends TreeContribution<T>
    A type of contribution for items in a ModularTreeView. Loosely based on ideas from Eclipse CNF

    • Method Detail

      • configureCell

        void configureCell(T data,
                   String text,
                   String supplementalText,
                   TreeCellImpl cell)
        Used to change the default cell configuration strategy.

        Here is also a good place to mark a cell with a pseudo-class to flag for custom css styling.

        Parameters:
        data - the data contents of the cell
        text - the main text representation of the tree item
        supplementalText - supplemental text information for the tree item
        cell - the cell object this item contribution is being applied to

      • deconfigureCell

        default void deconfigureCell(TreeCellImpl cell)
        Remove any configuration applied by configureCell(Object, String, String, TreeCellImpl), such as application of pseudo-classes and registration of context menus.
        Parameters:
        cell - the cell object this item contribution is being applied to
